FAQS

What is this website?
This is a website for those struggling and is made to help find resources to benefit the community as a whole.

Who is this for?
This website is mainly for those who are struggling, including everyone but also can be for people willing to volunteer.

What kinds of community resources do you offer?
We provide information on a wide range of community resources, including food assistance, housing support, healthcare services, mental health resources, employment and job training, education, legal aid, and family support. Available resources may vary by location.

Is this service free?
Yes. This website is completely free to use. Some of the organizations listed may have their own eligibility requirements or fees, but we aim to highlight low-cost and free services whenever possible.

Do I need to create an account to use the site?
No. You do not need to create an account to browse or search for resources. You can access the information anonymously.

Do I need to live in a specific area?
Many resources are location-specific, but some are available regionally or nationwide. You can use the search bar to find services available near you.

Are there age requirements?
Although some resources are designed for specific age groups, such as children, youth, adults, or seniors, they are made for anyone.

How often is the information updated?
We regularly review and update our listings to keep information as accurate as possible. However, availability and details can change, so we recommend confirming directly with the organization.

Can I contact the organizations directly through this site?
We provide contact information for each organization whenever possible, so you can reach out to them directly by phone, email, or instagram.

Do I need a referral?
Most resources do not require a referral, but some specialized services may. Any referral requirements will be noted in the listing, or you can confirm by contacting the organization directly.









